# Jira MCP — Use ONLY `user-mcp-jira-personal`

## THE RULE

Every single Jira MCP call in this repository MUST use server **`user-mcp-jira-personal`**.

There are exactly two Jira MCP servers available. The correct one is:

```
✅  user-mcp-jira-personal   ← ALWAYS use this one
❌  user-mcp-jira-work       ← NEVER use this one here
```

This applies to **every operation without exception**: search, create, read, update, comment, transition, sprint, board, link, worklog — everything.

---

## BEFORE EVERY JIRA CALL — MANDATORY CHECK

1. Look at the `server` argument you are about to pass.
2. If it is not `user-mcp-jira-personal`, stop. Correct it. Then call.

There is no scenario in this repo where `user-mcp-jira-work` is the right choice.

---

## Why

`user-mcp-jira-work` connects to a separate professional Jira workspace. Calling it from this repo writes personal project data into a work environment, which cannot be undone by the agent. This is a hard, permanent mistake.

---

## Quick Reference

| Operation | Server to use |
|---|---|
| `jira_search` / `jira_get_issue` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_create_issue` / `jira_batch_create_issues` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_update_issue` / `jira_delete_issue` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_add_comment` / `jira_edit_comment` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_transition_issue` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_create_issue_link` / `jira_remove_issue_link` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| `jira_create_sprint` / `jira_get_sprints_from_board` | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
| Any other Jira tool | `user-mcp-jira-personal` |
